CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 26, 1959, page 24, reads: "Guild Members and Guests get together during the Holly Ball at the Hilton Hotel as the Urban League Guild turns Pittsburgh socialites into a glittering dance throng in the Grand Ballroom. Standing, center rear, is Richard S. Dowdy, urban league staff member who has been active as a UL connections link between the guild and the parent body since the guild's founding. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Urban League members, including Richard S. Dowdy standing center, Wendell Freeland on right, and possibly Betty Tibbs wearing dark dress seated near center, gathered in Hilton Hotel, Downtown
